State Privacy Disclosures
Effective as of February 27, 2020.
1. California and Delaware “Do Not Track” Disclosure
California and Delaware law require Ritchie Bros. to indicate whether it honors “Do Not Track” settings in your browser. Ritchie Bros. does not monitor or respond to Do Not Track browser requests because there currently isn’t an industry or legal standard for recognizing or honoring them. We await the result of work by the privacy community and industry to determine when such a response is appropriate and what form it should take.
2. California Civil Code §1798.83 (“Shine the Light” Law)
While Ritchie Bros.’ solutions are generally not targeted at individuals buying or selling for personal, family or household purposes, individuals do engage with certain of our solutions from time to time for these purposes. Ritchie Bros. provides California residents who engage with our solutions in California for these purposes the right to request once per calendar year a list (names and addresses) of those third parties who we disclosed personal information to during the preceding calendar year for the third parties’ direct marketing purposes along with the categories of personal information provided. The information provided will be general in nature; not associated with the specific individual making the request. To exercise this right, use our dedicated
privacy contact form
. If specific information is desired, consider exercising available rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act described below.
3. California Consumer Privacy Act (“CCPA”)
This notice describes the rights of California consumers under the CCPA. We fully describe our practices in our
Privacy Statement
but use this separate notice to meet the CCPA’s requirements.
Sections 3A, 3B and 3C detail how we collect, share or “sell” (as defined by the CCPA) personal information of California consumers. Section 3D describes the rights of California consumers under CCPA and how to exercise them.
A. Collection of personal information
The following table identifies the personal information categories set out in the CCPA that we collect, the corresponding category of personal information referenced in the
Privacy Statement
and the information sources:
